TableContextTimeStampAfterTable: {32226=2012 Season: Was named honorable mention all-Big Sky after ranking second on the team with 97 tackles...led the team with 50 solo tackles, was second with two forced fumbles and tied for second with six pass breakups...started all 11 games and recorded at least four tackles in each contest...had four games with 10-plus tackles and eight with eight or more...tallied 14 tackles against North Dakota and 12 in the victory over Cal Poly...picked off a pass against Northern Colorado for his first career interception...had a sack at Idaho State and a half-sack at Eastern Washington. 2011 Season: Ranked second on the team with 86 total tackles…his 47 solo tackles were tied with Todd Davis for the team lead…tallied 3.5 tackles-for-loss, including a sack…also had five pass break-ups and blocked a punt…had at least four tackles in every game…recorded nine or more tackles in each of the first five games…had 12 tackles in the win over Montana and 10 stops at Oregon State and at Montana State. Prior to Sacramento State: Was a member of the USC football team for three seasons (2008-10)…played during the 2008 and 2009 seasons while redshirting in 2010…as a sophomore, he appeared in all 13 of the Trojans’ games and recorded nine tackles…led the team in special teams tackles. High School: A 2008 graduate of Damien HS in LaVerne, Calif…recorded 77 tackles as senior while also rushing for 257 yards and seven touchdowns…had at least eight tackles in seven of the team’s 10 games…tallied 10 stops against Poly, Glendora and Chino…also had a pair of interceptions and forced a fumble…played both receiver and running back on offense…caught 11 passes for 168 yards and a TD…returned a kickoff 94 yards for a TD against Poly and had a 95-yard return for a score against Los Altos. Personal: Majoring in communication studies…parents are Patrick and Sandy McMahon.}
